title: How has the proportion of timely antenatal assessments changed?
analysis_commentary: The proportion of antenatal appointments which happened before 12 weeks and six days has increased over time from a low of 80.0% in quarter 4 2009/10 to 86.9% in quarter 1 2012/13. This is an increase of nearly 7.0% in just over two years.
data_source: Health & Social Care Information Centre, Maternity (Vital signs)
